Analysis of antenatal smoking

smokers <- read_csv(here("data_clean/antenatal_smoking.csv")) %>% 
  arrange(year)

 Column specification 
cols(
  reference_area = col_character(),
  year = col_double(),
  ratio = col_double()
)
smokers %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = ratio) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 2002:2019) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, NA)) +
  geom_smooth(method=lm , color="red", se = FALSE) +
  labs(x = "Year",
       y = "Percentage of antenatal smokers",
       title = "What proportion of new mothers in Scotland are smokers?",
       subtitle = "Based on self-reported information obtained from mothers at their ante-natal visit")

Low birthweight analysis

low_birthweight <- read_csv(here("data_clean/low_birthweight.csv")) %>% 
  filter(measurement == "Ratio") %>% 
  arrange(year)

 Column specification 
cols(
  feature_code = col_character(),
  date_code = col_character(),
  measurement = col_character(),
  units = col_character(),
  value = col_double(),
  birth_weight = col_character(),
  year = col_double()
)
low_birthweight <- low_birthweight %>% 
  left_join(smokers,
            by = "year")  %>% 
  rename(smoker_ratio = ratio)
low_birthweight %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = smoker_ratio,
      y = value,) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm , color="red") +
  labs(x = "Percentage of antenatal smokers",
       y = "Percentage of low-weight births",
       title = "Is there a relationship between low birthweight and smoking?",
       subtitle = "Plot of low birthweight % vs smoking %, Scotland 2002 - 2019")

Age vs low-birthweight

low_birthweight <- low_birthweight %>% 
  left_join(older_mothers,
            by = "year") %>% 
  rename(older_ratio = ratio)

  ggplot() +

      y = value,) +

breastfeeding <- read_csv(here("data_clean/breastfeeding.csv")) %>% 
  filter(measurement == "Ratio",
         population_group == "Breastfed",
         breastfeeding_data_collection_time == "6 To 8 Week Review") %>% 
  rename(breastfeed_ratio = value) %>% 
  arrange(year)
breastfeeding %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = breastfeed_ratio) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 2002:2019) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, NA)) +
  geom_smooth(method=lm , color="red", se = FALSE) +
  labs(x = "Year",
       y = "Percentage of babies breastfed",
       title = "Are more babies being breastfed?")

bmi_scotland <- read_csv(here("data_clean/bmi_clinical.csv")) %>% 
  filter(weight_category == "Clinical - Overweight, Obese & Severely Obese") %>% 
  filter(hb_name == "Scotland",
         gender == "All",
         measurement == "Ratio")  %>% 
  rename(bmi_ratio = value)

 Column specification 
cols(
  feature_code = col_character(),
  date_code = col_character(),
  measurement = col_character(),
  units = col_character(),
  value = col_double(),
  gender = col_character(),
  weight_category = col_character(),
  year = col_double(),
  hb_name = col_character()
)
bmi_scotland %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = bmi_ratio) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 2002:2019) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, NA)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(x = "Year",
       y = "% Overweight / Obese / Severely Obese",
       title = "How many Primary 1 children have high BMI?",
       subtitle = "Children in Scotland, 2002 - 2019")

bmi_healthboard <- read_csv(here("data_clean/bmi_clinical.csv")) %>% 
  filter(weight_category == "Clinical - Overweight, Obese & Severely Obese") %>% 
  filter(hb_name != "Scotland",
         gender == "All",
         measurement == "Ratio")  %>% 
  rename(bmi_ratio = value)
bmi_healthboard %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = bmi_ratio,
      group = hb_name,
      colour = hb_name) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, NA)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(x = "Year",
       y = "% Overweight / Obese / Severely Obese",
       title = "How many Primary 1 children have high BMI?",
       subtitle = "Children in Scotland, 2002 - 2019",
       colour = "Health Board")
